---
import Layout from "../layouts/Layout.astro";
import Header from "../components/Header.astro";
import Footer from "../components/Footer.astro";
import "../styles/global.css";
---

<Layout title="Getting Started - Helpmaton">
  <Header />
  <main class="min-h-screen bg-neutral-50 p-8 py-16">
    <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto">
      <div class="mb-12 text-center">
        <h1 class="text-display-2 font-display text-neutral-900 mb-4">
          Getting Started
        </h1>
        <p class="text-lg text-neutral-600">
          Your journey to AI agent mastery starts here
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="space-y-6">
        <section
          class="bg-white rounded-lg shadow-soft p-6 border border-neutral-200"
        >
          <div class="flex items-center gap-3 mb-4">
            <span class="text-2xl font-semibold text-primary-600">1</span>
            <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-neutral-900">
              Create Your Account
            </h2>
          </div>
          <p class="mb-4 text-neutral-600">
            First things first - sign up for Helpmaton. Start with the free
            plan, or try paid plans with a 7-day trial. No credit card required.
          </p>
          <ol
            class="list-decimal list-inside space-y-2 text-sm text-neutral-600 ml-4"
          >
            <li>Click the "Start Your 7-Day Trial" button on the homepage</li>
            <li>Enter your email address and create a password</li>
            <li>Verify your email (check your spam folder)</li>
            <li>You're in! Welcome to Helpmaton</li>
          </ol>
          <div class="mt-4">
            <a
              href="https://app.helpmaton.com"
              class="inline-block bg-primary-600 text-white px-4 py-2 font-medium rounded-lg hover:bg-primary-700 transition-colors text-sm shadow-soft"
            >
              Sign Up Now â†’
            </a>
          </div>
        </section>

        <section
          class="bg-white rounded-lg shadow-soft p-6 border border-neutral-200"
        >
          <div class="flex items-center gap-3 mb-4">
            <span class="text-2xl font-semibold text-primary-600">2</span>
            <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-neutral-900">
              Create Your First Workspace
            </h2>
          </div>
          <p class="mb-4 text-neutral-600">
            Workspaces are containers where your AI agents live. Each workspace
            has its own settings, credits, and team members.
          </p>
          <ol
            class="list-decimal list-inside space-y-2 text-sm text-neutral-600 ml-4"
          >
            <li>After logging in, click "Create Workspace"</li>
            <li>Give it a name</li>
            <li>
              Set your spending limits for AI provider calls (optional, but
              recommended)
            </li>
            <li>Invite team members if needed (optional)</li>
            <li>Click "Create" to finish</li>
          </ol>
          <div
            class="mt-4 p-4 bg-primary-50 border border-primary-200 rounded-lg"
          >
            <p class="text-sm font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">
              Important: AI Provider Setup
            </p>
            <p class="text-sm text-neutral-700 mb-2">
              To use AI agents, you'll need to handle AI provider costs (OpenAI,
              Anthropic, Google, etc.). These are <strong
                >separate from your Helpmaton subscription</strong
              >. You have two flexible options:
            </p>
            <ul
              class="list-disc list-inside space-y-1 text-sm text-neutral-700 ml-4 mb-2"
            >
              <li>
                <strong>BYOK (Bring Your Own Key):</strong> Use your own LLM API keys
                and pay providers directly - you get all Helpmaton features while
                maintaining direct billing relationships
              </li>
              <li>
                <strong>Purchase credits:</strong> Buy credits through Helpmaton for
                usage-based billing with transparent pricing
              </li>
            </ul>
            <p class="text-xs text-neutral-600 mt-2">
              Your Helpmaton subscription covers the platform (hosting, memory,
              analytics, etc.); AI provider calls are billed separately. Set
              spending limits for budget control.
            </p>
          </div>
        </section>

        <section
          class="bg-white rounded-lg shadow-soft p-6 border border-neutral-200"
        >
          <div class="flex items-center gap-3 mb-4">
            <span class="text-2xl font-semibold text-primary-600">3</span>
            <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-neutral-900">
              Create Your First Agent
            </h2>
          </div>
          <p class="mb-4 text-neutral-600">
            Now for the fun part - creating your first AI agent! This is where
            the magic happens.
          </p>
          <ol
            class="list-decimal list-inside space-y-2 text-sm text-neutral-600 ml-4"
          >
            <li>Navigate to your workspace</li>
            <li>Click "Create Agent"</li>
            <li>Give your agent a name and personality</li>
            <li>Configure what your agent can do (its capabilities)</li>
            <li>Set up any initial instructions or prompts</li>
            <li>Click "Create" to finish</li>
          </ol>
          <p class="mt-4 text-sm text-neutral-500">
            Pro tip: Start simple! You can always add more complexity later.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section
          class="bg-white rounded-lg shadow-soft p-6 border border-neutral-200"
        >
          <div class="flex items-center gap-3 mb-4">
            <span class="text-2xl font-semibold text-primary-600">4</span>
            <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-neutral-900">
              Upload Documents
            </h2>
          </div>
          <p class="mb-4 text-neutral-600">
            Give your agents knowledge by uploading documents. They'll read and
            learn from everything you provide.
          </p>
          <ol
            class="list-decimal list-inside space-y-2 text-sm text-neutral-600 ml-4"
          >
            <li>Go to the "Documents" section in your workspace</li>
            <li>Click "Upload Document"</li>
            <li>Select your file (PDF, TXT, DOCX, and more)</li>
            <li>Organize documents into folders if needed</li>
            <li>Your agents can now access this knowledge</li>
          </ol>
          <p class="mt-4 text-sm text-neutral-500">
            Supported formats: PDF, TXT, DOCX, MD, CSV, and more
          </p>
        </section>

        <section
          class="bg-white rounded-lg shadow-soft p-6 border border-neutral-200"
        >
          <div class="flex items-center gap-3 mb-4">
            <span class="text-2xl font-semibold text-primary-600">5</span>
            <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-neutral-900">
              Test Your Agent
            </h2>
          </div>
          <p class="mb-4 text-neutral-600">
            Time to see your agent in action! Test it out and make sure
            everything works as expected.
          </p>
          <ol
            class="list-decimal list-inside space-y-2 text-sm text-neutral-600 ml-4"
          >
            <li>Go to your agent's page</li>
            <li>Use the test interface to send a message</li>
            <li>Watch your agent respond</li>
            <li>Adjust settings if needed</li>
            <li>Repeat until you're satisfied</li>
          </ol>
        </section>

        <section
          class="bg-white rounded-lg shadow-soft p-6 border border-neutral-200"
        >
          <div class="flex items-center gap-3 mb-4">
            <span class="text-2xl font-semibold text-primary-600">6</span>
            <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-neutral-900">
              Set Up Webhooks & Streaming (Optional)
            </h2>
          </div>
          <p class="mb-4 text-neutral-600">
            Connect your agent to the real world with webhooks. This lets your
            agent send and receive messages from external systems. Use streaming
            endpoints for real-time responses.
          </p>
          <ol
            class="list-decimal list-inside space-y-2 text-sm text-neutral-600 ml-4"
          >
            <li>Go to "Webhooks" in your workspace settings</li>
            <li>Click "Create Webhook" or set up streaming</li>
            <li>
              Enter your endpoint URL (for webhooks) or configure streaming
            </li>
            <li>Configure which events should trigger the webhook</li>
            <li>Test it out</li>
          </ol>
          <p class="mt-4 text-sm text-neutral-500">
            This step is optional - you can always add webhooks and streaming
            later!
          </p>
        </section>

        <section
          class="bg-white rounded-lg shadow-soft p-6 border border-neutral-200"
        >
          <div class="flex items-center gap-3 mb-4">
            <span class="text-2xl font-semibold text-primary-600">7</span>
            <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-neutral-900">
              Extend with MCP Servers (Optional)
            </h2>
          </div>
          <p class="mb-4 text-neutral-600">
            Power up your agents by connecting them to external tools and
            services via MCP (Model Context Protocol) servers. Enable your
            agents to call external APIs, query databases, and execute custom
            business logic.
          </p>
          <ol
            class="list-decimal list-inside space-y-2 text-sm text-neutral-600 ml-4"
          >
            <li>Go to "MCP Servers" in your workspace settings</li>
            <li>Click "Create MCP Server"</li>
            <li>Enter the server URL and configure authentication</li>
            <li>Enable the MCP server for your agents</li>
            <li>Your agents can now use external tools!</li>
          </ol>
          <p class="mt-4 text-sm text-neutral-500">
            This is an advanced feature - perfect for when you need to integrate
            with external systems!
          </p>
        </section>

        <section
          class="bg-white rounded-lg shadow-soft p-6 border border-neutral-200"
        >
          <div class="flex items-center gap-3 mb-4">
            <span class="text-2xl font-semibold text-primary-600">8</span>
            <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-neutral-900">
              Enable Web Search & Content Extraction (Optional)
            </h2>
          </div>
          <p class="mb-4 text-neutral-600">
            Give your agents access to real-time, up-to-date information beyond their training data. Enable web search to find current information, news, and articles. Extract and summarize content from any web page URL. Perfect for research assistants, news monitoring, and content analysis workflows.
          </p>
          <ol
            class="list-decimal list-inside space-y-2 text-sm text-neutral-600 ml-4"
          >
            <li>Go to your agent's configuration page</li>
            <li>Find the "Web Search" and "Content Extraction" toggles</li>
            <li>Enable the features you want (web search, content extraction, or both)</li>
            <li>Your agents can now search the web and extract content from URLs!</li>
          </ol>
          <div
            class="mt-4 p-4 bg-primary-50 border border-primary-200 rounded-lg"
          >
            <p class="text-sm font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">
              Web Search Pricing
            </p>
            <p class="text-sm text-neutral-700 mb-2">
              All plans include <strong>10 free web search calls per 24 hours</strong>. Additional calls are billed at <strong>$0.008 per call</strong>. This gives you access to real-time information at a transparent, cost-effective rate.
            </p>
            <p class="text-xs text-neutral-600 mt-2">
              Perfect for research assistants, news monitoring, and content analysis workflows that need current information beyond training data.
            </p>
          </div>
          <p class="mt-4 text-sm text-neutral-500">
            This step is optional - you can always enable web search features later!
          </p>
        </section>

        <section
          class="bg-white rounded-lg shadow-soft p-6 border border-neutral-200"
        >
          <div class="flex items-center gap-3 mb-4">
            <span class="text-2xl font-semibold text-primary-600">9</span>
            <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-neutral-900">
              Explore Memory & Analytics (Automatic)
            </h2>
          </div>
          <p class="mb-4 text-neutral-600">
            Your agents automatically benefit from advanced features built into
            Helpmaton. No additional setup required!
          </p>
          <ul
            class="list-disc list-inside space-y-2 text-sm text-neutral-600 ml-4"
          >
            <li>
              <strong>Agent Memory:</strong> Agents remember facts, people, and events
              through stratified memory architecture with progressive summarization
            </li>
            <li>
              <strong>Usage Analytics:</strong> Track token usage (prompt, completion,
              reasoning, cached) with daily/hourly aggregation and historical data
            </li>
            <li>
              <strong>Cost Control:</strong> Set spending limits at workspace and
              agent levels to maintain budget control
            </li>
          </ul>
          <p class="mt-4 text-sm text-neutral-500">
            These features work automatically based on your subscription plan!
          </p>
        </section>

        <section
          class="bg-gradient-primary rounded-lg shadow-colored p-6 text-white"
        >
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold mb-4">You're All Set!</h2>
          <p class="mb-4 text-white/90">
            Congratulations! You've created your first workspace, agent, and
            uploaded documents. You're ready to get started with Helpmaton!
          </p>
          <p class="mb-4 text-white/90">
            Want to learn more? Check out our full documentation or join our
            community.
          </p>
          <div class="flex gap-4 flex-wrap">
            <a
              href="/documentation"
              class="inline-block bg-white text-primary-600 px-4 py-2 font-medium rounded-lg hover:bg-neutral-50 transition-colors text-sm shadow-soft"
            >
              Full Documentation
            </a>
            <a
              href="https://app.helpmaton.com/docs/api"
              target="_blank"
              rel="noopener noreferrer"
              class="inline-block border-2 border-white bg-transparent text-white px-4 py-2 font-medium rounded-lg hover:bg-white hover:text-primary-600 transition-colors text-sm"
            >
              API Reference
            </a>
            <a
              href="https://discord.gg/Zf9Q7GpuKx"
              target="_blank"
              rel="noopener noreferrer"
              class="inline-block border-2 border-white bg-transparent text-white px-4 py-2 font-medium rounded-lg hover:bg-white hover:text-primary-600 transition-colors text-sm"
            >
              Join Discord
            </a>
          </div>
        </section>
      </div>
    </div>
  </main>
  <Footer />
</Layout>
